VERDICT: REJECTED
The task should not be marked complete because the committed diff does not implement the stated setup/UI work and includes only non-product changes.

Critical findings:
- The only meaningful tracked project change in the commit range is `.replit` (`modules` adds `bash`).
- No committed changes were made to application source files for the claimed hero/chapters improvements. The visible `app/chapters/page.tsx` updates exist only as uncommitted working-tree edits, so they are not part of the completed task deliverable.
- The commit range is dominated by deletions under `.local/*` (tooling/state/skills files), which are unrelated to the task objective and add high noise/risk to the review surface without delivering user-facing functionality.
- Validation is not complete: a production build currently fails (`npm run build` exits non-zero), so “setup verified” is not substantiated by the committed state.

Security: none observed in app code changes relevant to this task.

Next actions:
1) Commit only the intended product changes (e.g., `app/chapters/page.tsx` and any real dependency/config updates needed), and exclude `.local/*` state/tooling churn from task commits.
2) Re-run and pass required verification in the same committed state (`npm run dev` smoke + `npm run build`), then report those results.
3) Re-submit for review with a focused diff tied directly to Task #1 acceptance criteria.

